main event: Two USAF officers reported observing an unidentified flying object near Tillamook, Oregon on 9 June 1953.
interesting points: The object was described as half-moon in shape and white in color., It was viewed for approximately 5 hours through binoculars., No manner of propulsion was observed, and it appeared to hover during the observation., The sighting was later concluded by Project Blue Book's astronomers to be the planet Venus., The object was estimated to be about 25 feet in diameter and moved in a north-westerly direction.
witness description: USAF officers stationed with the 120th Fighter Interceptor Squadron detachment
